opaqueness

opaqueness: number = 1
  • Defined in davinci-newton/view/SimView.ts:90

The transparency used when painting the drawables; a number between 0.0 (fully transparent) and 1.0 (fully opaque).

    • Defined in davinci-newton/view/SimView.ts:295

zoomIn

  • zoomIn(): void
    • Defined in davinci-newton/view/SimView.ts:439

    Makes the height of the simulation rectangle smaller by fraction 1/{@link #zoom}, and also the width if {@link #getScaleTogether} is true. Also broadcasts a {@link #SIM_RECT_CHANGED} event.

    Returns void

zoomOut

  • zoomOut(): void
    • Defined in davinci-newton/view/SimView.ts:448

    Makes the height of the simulation rectangle bigger by fraction {@link #zoom}, and also the width if {@link #getScaleTogether} is true. Also broadcasts a {@link #SIM_RECT_CHANGED} event.

    Returns void
